data.value:
Order of Operation
1. Goto camera web page and set Exposure to minimum. Now vary Saturation and Contrast until target shows up brightly and with a slight green color.
2. Select the camera on the Target tab and click the Start button to start seeing the video stream.
3. Check the box to Show filter frame and manipulate the Hue, Saturation and Luminance low and high thresholds until the target is well defined.
4. If there will be multiple targets of different sizes, use the Area filter, Aspect Ratio filter, Width filter or Height filter.
5. Once the target is well-defined and repeatable, goto the Calibration tab to calibrate the Distance value. Enter the height of your target and how far it is from your camera. Press the Calibration button and the correct distance should now be displayed on screen.
6. Go to the Setup tab and press the Save button to save your settings. These settings will be automatically loaded the next time you start the application.
